# RAY_memory_usage_threshold=0.90 by a small margin (0.002205).
#
# Attempts 14A (VLLM_CUTLASS) and 14B (FLASHINFER_CUTLASS) explored
# alternative NvFp4 MoE backends to avoid the MARLIN init RSS spike:
#   - 14A: VLLM_CUTLASS rejected before weight loading --
#     CutlassExpertsFp4._supports_parallel_config() requires ep_size == 1
#     (this deployment uses ep_size=2).
#   - 14B: FLASHINFER_CUTLASS passed device/quant-scheme/parallel-config
#     checks and EP init (144/288 experts/rank), but was rejected during
#     FusedMoE layer construction because FlashInferExperts does not support
#     MoEActivation.SWIGLUSTEP (Step-3.7-Flash-NVFP4's actual activation).
#
# A full activation-aware re-check of all remaining NvFp4 MoE backends
# (FLASHINFER_B12X, FLASHINFER_TRTLLM, FLASHINFER_CUTEDSL,
# FLASHINFER_CUTEDSL_BATCHED, VLLM_CUTLASS, EMULATION) against this
# deployment's requirements (SM121/device-family-120, NVFP4 static/dynamic,
# EP size 2, allgather_reducescatter, MoEActivation.SWIGLUSTEP) found that
# MARLIN is the ONLY backend that satisfies all of them:
#   - FLASHINFER_B12X: _supports_activation == SILU only -> rejects
#     SWIGLUSTEP.
#   - FLASHINFER_TRTLLM / FLASHINFER_CUTEDSL (and by extension
#     FLASHINFER_CUTEDSL_BATCHED): _supports_current_device() requires
#     is_device_capability_family(100); GB10 is family 120 -> rejected before
#     activation checks even apply. CUTEDSL's _supports_activation is also
#     SILU-only.
#   - VLLM_CUTLASS: supports SWIGLUSTEP, but _supports_parallel_config()
#     requires ep_size == 1 (already confirmed rejected in 14A).
#   - FLASHINFER_CUTLASS: confirmed rejected for SWIGLUSTEP in 14B.
#   - EMULATION: not run -- MARLIN already satisfies every structural
#     requirement; Attempt 13's failure was a Ray object-store memory
#     accounting margin (0.002205 over threshold), not an
#     activation/device/EP incompatibility that EMULATION could diagnose.
#     EMULATION would add dequant overhead without addressing the margin.
#
# Backend substitution is therefore exhausted: MARLIN (the backend
# auto-selected in Attempt 13) remains the only viable NvFp4 MoE backend for
# this deployment, and the Attempt 13 failure must be addressed via memory
# accounting / margin, not backend choice.
#
# Attempt 15A changes ONLY:
#
#   RAY_OBJECT_STORE_MEMORY_BYTES: 4294967296 (4 GiB) -> 1073741824 (1 GiB)
#
# Rationale: Attempt 13's Ray OOM (0.902205) exceeded the 0.90 threshold by
# only ~0.27GiB-equivalent (0.002205 * 121.63GiB). Ray's memory-usage ratio
# is computed against total node memory and includes the object store's
# reserved share of the head node's baseline footprint. Reducing the
# object-store reservation from 4 GiB to 1 GiB lowers Ray's own baseline
# memory footprint on the head node by ~3 GiB, which may be enough margin
# for MARLIN's MoE-init RSS spike (~5.77-6.17 GiB observed in Attempt 13) to
# complete without crossing 0.90. This does NOT change MoE backend selection
# (MARLIN remains auto-selected), EP configuration, KV-cache sizing, or any
# other Attempt 13 setting.
#
# Interpretation:
#   - If Ray OOM no longer occurs and MoE init / KV-cache stages complete ->
#     reducing head-node Ray baseline memory was sufficient margin; MARLIN +
#     fixed-KV + EP is viable with this Ray tuning.
#   - If Ray OOM recurs at a lower/later usage ratio -> object-store
#     reservation was a contributing but not sole factor; the MARLIN MoE-init
#     RSS spike itself needs further reduction (e.g. lower
#     GPU_MEMORY_UTILIZATION in a separate variant -- do not change it here).
#   - If Ray OOM recurs at essentially the same ratio -> object-store
#     reservation was not a meaningful factor in the 0.902205 margin; some
#     other Ray/host baseline accounting dominates.
#
# DO NOT raise RAY_memory_usage_threshold above 0.90 in this file or in
